2027static int calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_vbr(const VP9_COMP *const cpi) {
2028 static const int kf_ratio = 25;
2029 const RATE_CONTROL *rc = &cpi->rc;
2030 const int target = rc->avg_frame_bandwidth * kf_ratio;
2031 return vp9_rc_clamp_iframe_target_size(cpi, target);
2032}
2033
2034static void adjust_gfint_frame_constraint(VP9_COMP *cpi, int frame_constraint) {
2035 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2036 rc->constrained_gf_group = 0;
2037 // Reset gf interval to make more equal spacing for frame_constraint.
2038 if ((frame_constraint <= 7 * rc->baseline_gf_interval >> 2) &&
2039 (frame_constraint > rc->baseline_gf_interval)) {
2040 rc->baseline_gf_interval = frame_constraint >> 1;
2041 if (rc->baseline_gf_interval < 5)
2042 rc->baseline_gf_interval = frame_constraint;
2043 rc->constrained_gf_group = 1;
2044 } else {
2045 // Reset to keep gf_interval <= frame_constraint.
2046 if (rc->baseline_gf_interval > frame_constraint) {
2047 rc->baseline_gf_interval = frame_constraint;
2048 rc->constrained_gf_group = 1;
2049 }
2050 }
2051}
2052
2053void vp9_rc_get_one_pass_vbr_params(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2054 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2055 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2056 int target;
2057 if (!cpi->refresh_alt_ref_frame &&
2058 (cm->current_video_frame == 0 || (cpi->frame_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY) ||
2059 rc->frames_to_key == 0)) {
2060 cm->frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
2061 rc->this_key_frame_forced =
2062 cm->current_video_frame != 0 && rc->frames_to_key == 0;
2063 rc->frames_to_key = cpi->oxcf.key_freq;
2064 rc->kf_boost = DEFAULT_KF_BOOST;
2065 rc->source_alt_ref_active = 0;
2066 } else {
2067 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
2068 }
2069 if (rc->frames_till_gf_update_due == 0) {
2070 double rate_err = 1.0;
2071 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST;
2072 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ && cpi->oxcf.pass == 0) {
2073 vp9_cyclic_refresh_set_golden_update(cpi);
2074 } else {
2075 rc->baseline_gf_interval = VPXMIN(
2076 20, VPXMAX(10, (rc->min_gf_interval + rc->max_gf_interval) / 2));
2077 }
2078 rc->af_ratio_onepass_vbr = 10;
2079 if (rc->rolling_target_bits > 0)
2080 rate_err =
2081 (double)rc->rolling_actual_bits / (double)rc->rolling_target_bits;
2082 if (cm->current_video_frame > 30) {
2083 if (rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] > (7 * rc->worst_quality) >> 3 &&
2084 rate_err > 3.5) {
2085 rc->baseline_gf_interval =
2086 VPXMIN(15, (3 * rc->baseline_gf_interval) >> 1);
2087 } else if (rc->avg_frame_low_motion < 20) {
2088 // Decrease gf interval for high motion case.
2089 rc->baseline_gf_interval = VPXMAX(6, rc->baseline_gf_interval >> 1);
2090 }
2091 // Adjust boost and af_ratio based on avg_frame_low_motion, which varies
2092 // between 0 and 100 (stationary, 100% zero/small motion).
2093 rc->gfu_boost =
2094 VPXMAX(500, DEFAULT_GF_BOOST * (rc->avg_frame_low_motion << 1) /
2095 (rc->avg_frame_low_motion + 100));
2096 rc->af_ratio_onepass_vbr = VPXMIN(15, VPXMAX(5, 3 * rc->gfu_boost / 400));
2097 }
2098 adjust_gfint_frame_constraint(cpi, rc->frames_to_key);
2099 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2100 cpi->refresh_golden_frame = 1;
2101 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 0;
2102 rc->alt_ref_gf_group = 0;
2103 if (cpi->sf.use_altref_onepass && cpi->oxcf.enable_auto_arf) {
2104 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 1;
2105 rc->alt_ref_gf_group = 1;
2106 }
2107 }
2108 if (cm->frame_type == KEY_FRAME)
2109 target = calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_vbr(cpi);
2110 else
2111 target = calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_vbr(cpi);
2112 vp9_rc_set_frame_target(cpi, target);
2113 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ && cpi->oxcf.pass == 0)
2114 vp9_cyclic_refresh_update_parameters(cpi);
2115}
2116
2117int vp9_calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(const VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2118 const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2119 const RATE_CONTROL *rc = &cpi->rc;
2120 const SVC *const svc = &cpi->svc;
2121 const int64_t diff = rc->optimal_buffer_level - rc->buffer_level;
2122 const int64_t one_pct_bits = 1 + rc->optimal_buffer_level / 100;
2123 int min_frame_target =
2124 VPXMAX(rc->avg_frame_bandwidth >> 4, FRAME_OVERHEAD_BITS);
2125 int target;
2126
2127 if (oxcf->gf_cbr_boost_pct) {
2128 const int af_ratio_pct = oxcf->gf_cbr_boost_pct + 100;
2129 target = cpi->refresh_golden_frame
2130 ? (rc->avg_frame_bandwidth * rc->baseline_gf_interval *
2131 af_ratio_pct) /
2132 (rc->baseline_gf_interval * 100 + af_ratio_pct - 100)
2133 : (rc->avg_frame_bandwidth * rc->baseline_gf_interval * 100) /
2134 (rc->baseline_gf_interval * 100 + af_ratio_pct - 100);
2135 } else {
2136 target = rc->avg_frame_bandwidth;
2137 }
2138 if (is_one_pass_cbr_svc(cpi)) {
2139 // Note that for layers, avg_frame_bandwidth is the cumulative
2140 // per-frame-bandwidth. For the target size of this frame, use the
2141 // layer average frame size (i.e., non-cumulative per-frame-bw).
2142 int layer = LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(svc->spatial_layer_id, svc->temporal_layer_id,
2143 svc->number_temporal_layers);
2144 const LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = &svc->layer_context[layer];
2145 target = lc->avg_frame_size;
2146 min_frame_target = VPXMAX(lc->avg_frame_size >> 4, FRAME_OVERHEAD_BITS);
2147 }
2148 if (diff > 0) {
2149 // Lower the target bandwidth for this frame.
2150 const int pct_low = (int)VPXMIN(diff / one_pct_bits, oxcf->under_shoot_pct);
2151 target -= (target * pct_low) / 200;
2152 } else if (diff < 0) {
2153 // Increase the target bandwidth for this frame.
2154 const int pct_high =
2155 (int)VPXMIN(-diff / one_pct_bits, oxcf->over_shoot_pct);
2156 target += (target * pct_high) / 200;
2157 }
2158 if (oxcf->rc_max_inter_bitrate_pct) {
2159 const int max_rate =
2160 rc->avg_frame_bandwidth * oxcf->rc_max_inter_bitrate_pct / 100;
2161 target = VPXMIN(target, max_rate);
2162 }
2163 return VPXMAX(min_frame_target, target);
2164}
2165
2166int vp9_calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(const VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2167 const RATE_CONTROL *rc = &cpi->rc;
2168 const VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2169 const SVC *const svc = &cpi->svc;
2170 int target;
2171 if (cpi->common.current_video_frame == 0) {
2172 target = ((rc->starting_buffer_level / 2) > INT_MAX)
2173 ? INT_MAX
2174 : (int)(rc->starting_buffer_level / 2);
2175 } else {
2176 int kf_boost = 32;
2177 double framerate = cpi->framerate;
2178 if (svc->number_temporal_layers > 1 && oxcf->rc_mode == VPX_CBR) {
2179 // Use the layer framerate for temporal layers CBR mode.
2180 const int layer =
2181 LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(svc->spatial_layer_id, svc->temporal_layer_id,
2182 svc->number_temporal_layers);
2183 const LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = &svc->layer_context[layer];
2184 framerate = lc->framerate;
2185 }
2186 kf_boost = VPXMAX(kf_boost, (int)(2 * framerate - 16));
2187 if (rc->frames_since_key < framerate / 2) {
2188 kf_boost = (int)(kf_boost * rc->frames_since_key / (framerate / 2));
2189 }
2190 target = ((16 + kf_boost) * rc->avg_frame_bandwidth) >> 4;
2191 }
2192 return vp9_rc_clamp_iframe_target_size(cpi, target);
2193}
2194
2195static void set_intra_only_frame(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2196 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2197 SVC *const svc = &cpi->svc;
2198 // Don't allow intra_only frame for bypass/flexible SVC mode, or if number
2199 // of spatial layers is 1 or if number of spatial or temporal layers > 3.
2200 // Also if intra-only is inserted on very first frame, don't allow if
2201 // if number of temporal layers > 1. This is because on intra-only frame
2202 // only 3 reference buffers can be updated, but for temporal layers > 1
2203 // we generally need to use buffer slots 4 and 5.
2204 if ((cm->current_video_frame == 0 && svc->number_temporal_layers > 1) ||
2205 svc->temporal_layering_mode == VP9E_TEMPORAL_LAYERING_MODE_BYPASS ||
2206 svc->number_spatial_layers > 3 || svc->number_temporal_layers > 3 ||
2207 svc->number_spatial_layers == 1)
2208 return;
2209 cm->show_frame = 0;
2210 cm->intra_only = 1;
2211 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
2212 cpi->ext_refresh_frame_flags_pending = 1;
2213 cpi->ext_refresh_last_frame = 1;
2214 cpi->ext_refresh_golden_frame = 1;
2215 cpi->ext_refresh_alt_ref_frame = 1;
2216 if (cm->current_video_frame == 0) {
2217 cpi->lst_fb_idx = 0;
2218 cpi->gld_fb_idx = 1;
2219 cpi->alt_fb_idx = 2;
2220 } else {
2221 int i;
2222 int count = 0;
2223 cpi->lst_fb_idx = -1;
2224 cpi->gld_fb_idx = -1;
2225 cpi->alt_fb_idx = -1;
2226 // For intra-only frame we need to refresh all slots that were
2227 // being used for the base layer (fb_idx_base[i] == 1).
2228 // Start with assigning last first, then golden and then alt.
2229 for (i = 0; i < REF_FRAMES; ++i) {
2230 if (svc->fb_idx_base[i] == 1) count++;
2231 if (count == 1 && cpi->lst_fb_idx == -1) cpi->lst_fb_idx = i;
2232 if (count == 2 && cpi->gld_fb_idx == -1) cpi->gld_fb_idx = i;
2233 if (count == 3 && cpi->alt_fb_idx == -1) cpi->alt_fb_idx = i;
2234 }
2235 // If golden or alt is not being used for base layer, then set them
2236 // to the lst_fb_idx.
2237 if (cpi->gld_fb_idx == -1) cpi->gld_fb_idx = cpi->lst_fb_idx;
2238 if (cpi->alt_fb_idx == -1) cpi->alt_fb_idx = cpi->lst_fb_idx;
2239 }
2240}
2241
2242void vp9_rc_get_svc_params(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2243 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2244 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2245 SVC *const svc = &cpi->svc;
2246 int target = rc->avg_frame_bandwidth;
2247 int layer = LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(svc->spatial_layer_id, svc->temporal_layer_id,
2248 svc->number_temporal_layers);
2249 if (svc->first_spatial_layer_to_encode)
2250 svc->layer_context[svc->temporal_layer_id].is_key_frame = 0;
2251 // Periodic key frames is based on the super-frame counter
2252 // (svc.current_superframe), also only base spatial layer is key frame.
2253 // Key frame is set for any of the following: very first frame, frame flags
2254 // indicates key, superframe counter hits key frequency, or (non-intra) sync
2255 // flag is set for spatial layer 0.
2256 if ((cm->current_video_frame == 0 && !svc->previous_frame_is_intra_only) ||
2257 (cpi->frame_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY) ||
2258 (cpi->oxcf.auto_key &&
2259 (svc->current_superframe % cpi->oxcf.key_freq == 0) &&
2260 !svc->previous_frame_is_intra_only && svc->spatial_layer_id == 0) ||
2261 (svc->spatial_layer_sync[0] == 1 && svc->spatial_layer_id == 0)) {
2262 cm->frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
2263 rc->source_alt_ref_active = 0;
2264 if (is_one_pass_cbr_svc(cpi)) {
2265 if (cm->current_video_frame > 0) vp9_svc_reset_temporal_layers(cpi, 1);
2266 layer = LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(svc->spatial_layer_id, svc->temporal_layer_id,
2267 svc->number_temporal_layers);
2268 svc->layer_context[layer].is_key_frame = 1;
2269 cpi->ref_frame_flags &= (~VP9_LAST_FLAG & ~VP9_GOLD_FLAG & ~VP9_ALT_FLAG);
2270 // Assumption here is that LAST_FRAME is being updated for a keyframe.
2271 // Thus no change in update flags.
2272 target = vp9_calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2273 }
2274 } else {
2275 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
2276 if (is_one_pass_cbr_svc(cpi)) {
2277 LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = &svc->layer_context[layer];
2278 // Add condition current_video_frame > 0 for the case where first frame
2279 // is intra only followed by overlay/copy frame. In this case we don't
2280 // want to reset is_key_frame to 0 on overlay/copy frame.
2281 lc->is_key_frame =
2282 (svc->spatial_layer_id == 0 && cm->current_video_frame > 0)
2283 ? 0
2284 : svc->layer_context[svc->temporal_layer_id].is_key_frame;
2285 target = vp9_calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2286 }
2287 }
2288
2289 if (svc->simulcast_mode) {
2290 if (svc->spatial_layer_id > 0 &&
2291 svc->layer_context[layer].is_key_frame == 1) {
2292 cm->frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
2293 cpi->ref_frame_flags &= (~VP9_LAST_FLAG & ~VP9_GOLD_FLAG & ~VP9_ALT_FLAG);
2294 target = vp9_calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2295 }
2296 // Set the buffer idx and refresh flags for key frames in simulcast mode.
2297 // Note the buffer slot for long-term reference is set below (line 2255),
2298 // and alt_ref is used for that on key frame. So use last and golden for
2299 // the other two normal slots.
2300 if (cm->frame_type == KEY_FRAME) {
2301 if (svc->number_spatial_layers == 2) {
2302 if (svc->spatial_layer_id == 0) {
2303 cpi->lst_fb_idx = 0;
2304 cpi->gld_fb_idx = 2;
2305 cpi->alt_fb_idx = 6;
2306 } else if (svc->spatial_layer_id == 1) {
2307 cpi->lst_fb_idx = 1;
2308 cpi->gld_fb_idx = 3;
2309 cpi->alt_fb_idx = 6;
2310 }
2311 } else if (svc->number_spatial_layers == 3) {
2312 if (svc->spatial_layer_id == 0) {
2313 cpi->lst_fb_idx = 0;
2314 cpi->gld_fb_idx = 3;
2315 cpi->alt_fb_idx = 6;
2316 } else if (svc->spatial_layer_id == 1) {
2317 cpi->lst_fb_idx = 1;
2318 cpi->gld_fb_idx = 4;
2319 cpi->alt_fb_idx = 6;
2320 } else if (svc->spatial_layer_id == 2) {
2321 cpi->lst_fb_idx = 2;
2322 cpi->gld_fb_idx = 5;
2323 cpi->alt_fb_idx = 7;
2324 }
2325 }
2326 cpi->ext_refresh_last_frame = 1;
2327 cpi->ext_refresh_golden_frame = 1;
2328 cpi->ext_refresh_alt_ref_frame = 1;
2329 }
2330 }
2331
2332 // Check if superframe contains a sync layer request.
2333 vp9_svc_check_spatial_layer_sync(cpi);
2334
2335 // If long term termporal feature is enabled, set the period of the update.
2336 // The update/refresh of this reference frame is always on base temporal
2337 // layer frame.
2338 if (svc->use_gf_temporal_ref_current_layer) {
2339 // Only use gf long-term prediction on non-key superframes.
2340 if (!svc->layer_context[svc->temporal_layer_id].is_key_frame) {
2341 // Use golden for this reference, which will be used for prediction.
2342 int index = svc->spatial_layer_id;
2343 if (svc->number_spatial_layers == 3) index = svc->spatial_layer_id - 1;
2344 assert(index >= 0);
2345 cpi->gld_fb_idx = svc->buffer_gf_temporal_ref[index].idx;
2346 // Enable prediction off LAST (last reference) and golden (which will
2347 // generally be further behind/long-term reference).
2348 cpi->ref_frame_flags = VP9_LAST_FLAG | VP9_GOLD_FLAG;
2349 }
2350 // Check for update/refresh of reference: only refresh on base temporal
2351 // layer.
2352 if (svc->temporal_layer_id == 0) {
2353 if (svc->layer_context[svc->temporal_layer_id].is_key_frame) {
2354 // On key frame we update the buffer index used for long term reference.
2355 // Use the alt_ref since it is not used or updated on key frames.
2356 int index = svc->spatial_layer_id;
2357 if (svc->number_spatial_layers == 3) index = svc->spatial_layer_id - 1;
2358 assert(index >= 0);
2359 cpi->alt_fb_idx = svc->buffer_gf_temporal_ref[index].idx;
2360 cpi->ext_refresh_alt_ref_frame = 1;
2361 } else if (rc->frames_till_gf_update_due == 0) {
2362 // Set perdiod of next update. Make it a multiple of 10, as the cyclic
2363 // refresh is typically ~10%, and we'd like the update to happen after
2364 // a few cylces of the refresh (so it better quality frame). Note the
2365 // cyclic refresh for SVC only operates on base temporal layer frames.
2366 // Choose 20 as perdiod for now (2 cycles).
2367 rc->baseline_gf_interval = 20;
2368 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2369 cpi->ext_refresh_golden_frame = 1;
2370 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST;
2371 }
2372 }
2373 } else if (!svc->use_gf_temporal_ref) {
2374 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = INT_MAX;
2375 rc->baseline_gf_interval = INT_MAX;
2376 }
2377 if (svc->set_intra_only_frame) {
2378 set_intra_only_frame(cpi);
2379 target = vp9_calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2380 }
2381 // Any update/change of global cyclic refresh parameters (amount/delta-qp)
2382 // should be done here, before the frame qp is selected.
2383 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ)
2384 vp9_cyclic_refresh_update_parameters(cpi);
2385
2386 vp9_rc_set_frame_target(cpi, target);
2387 if (cm->show_frame) update_buffer_level_svc_preencode(cpi);
2388
2389 if (cpi->oxcf.resize_mode == RESIZE_DYNAMIC && svc->single_layer_svc == 1 &&
2390 svc->spatial_layer_id == svc->first_spatial_layer_to_encode &&
2391 svc->temporal_layer_id == 0) {
2392 LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = NULL;
2393 cpi->resize_pending = vp9_resize_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2394 if (cpi->resize_pending) {
2395 int tl, width, height;
2396 // Apply the same scale to all temporal layers.
2397 for (tl = 0; tl < svc->number_temporal_layers; tl++) {
2398 lc = &svc->layer_context[svc->spatial_layer_id *
2399 svc->number_temporal_layers +
2400 tl];
2401 lc->scaling_factor_num_resize =
2402 cpi->resize_scale_num * lc->scaling_factor_num;
2403 lc->scaling_factor_den_resize =
2404 cpi->resize_scale_den * lc->scaling_factor_den;
2405 // Reset rate control for all temporal layers.
2406 lc->rc.buffer_level = lc->rc.optimal_buffer_level;
2407 lc->rc.bits_off_target = lc->rc.optimal_buffer_level;
2408 lc->rc.rate_correction_factors[INTER_FRAME] =
2409 rc->rate_correction_factors[INTER_FRAME];
2410 }
2411 // Set the size for this current temporal layer.
2412 lc = &svc->layer_context[svc->spatial_layer_id *
2413 svc->number_temporal_layers +
2414 svc->temporal_layer_id];
2415 get_layer_resolution(cpi->oxcf.width, cpi->oxcf.height,
2416 lc->scaling_factor_num_resize,
2417 lc->scaling_factor_den_resize, &width, &height);
2418 vp9_set_size_literal(cpi, width, height);
2419 svc->resize_set = 1;
2420 }
2421 } else {
2422 cpi->resize_pending = 0;
2423 svc->resize_set = 0;
2424 }
2425}
2426
2427void vp9_rc_get_one_pass_cbr_params(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2428 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2429 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2430 int target;
2431 if ((cm->current_video_frame == 0) || (cpi->frame_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY) ||
2432 (cpi->oxcf.auto_key && rc->frames_to_key == 0)) {
2433 cm->frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
2434 rc->frames_to_key = cpi->oxcf.key_freq;
2435 rc->kf_boost = DEFAULT_KF_BOOST;
2436 rc->source_alt_ref_active = 0;
2437 } else {
2438 cm->frame_type = INTER_FRAME;
2439 }
2440 if (rc->frames_till_gf_update_due == 0) {
2441 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ)
2442 vp9_cyclic_refresh_set_golden_update(cpi);
2443 else
2444 rc->baseline_gf_interval =
2445 (rc->min_gf_interval + rc->max_gf_interval) / 2;
2446 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2447 // NOTE: frames_till_gf_update_due must be <= frames_to_key.
2448 if (rc->frames_till_gf_update_due > rc->frames_to_key)
2449 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->frames_to_key;
2450 cpi->refresh_golden_frame = 1;
2451 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST;
2452 }
2453
2454 // Any update/change of global cyclic refresh parameters (amount/delta-qp)
2455 // should be done here, before the frame qp is selected.
2456 if (cpi->oxcf.aq_mode == CYCLIC_REFRESH_AQ)
2457 vp9_cyclic_refresh_update_parameters(cpi);
2458
2459 if (frame_is_intra_only(cm))
2460 target = vp9_calc_iframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2461 else
2462 target = vp9_calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2463
2464 vp9_rc_set_frame_target(cpi, target);
2465
2466 if (cm->show_frame) vp9_update_buffer_level_preencode(cpi);
2467
2468 if (cpi->oxcf.resize_mode == RESIZE_DYNAMIC)
2469 cpi->resize_pending = vp9_resize_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2470 else
2471 cpi->resize_pending = 0;
2472}
2473
2474int vp9_compute_qdelta(const RATE_CONTROL *rc, double qstart, double qtarget,
2475 vpx_bit_depth_t bit_depth) {
2476 int start_index = rc->worst_quality;
2477 int target_index = rc->worst_quality;
2478 int i;
2479
2480 // Convert the average q value to an index.
2481 for (i = rc->best_quality; i < rc->worst_quality; ++i) {
2482 start_index = i;
2483 if (vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(i, bit_depth) >= qstart) break;
2484 }
2485
2486 // Convert the q target to an index
2487 for (i = rc->best_quality; i < rc->worst_quality; ++i) {
2488 target_index = i;
2489 if (vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(i, bit_depth) >= qtarget) break;
2490 }
2491
2492 return target_index - start_index;
2493}
2494
2495int vp9_compute_qdelta_by_rate(const RATE_CONTROL *rc, FRAME_TYPE frame_type,
2496 int qindex, double rate_target_ratio,
2497 vpx_bit_depth_t bit_depth) {
2498 int target_index = rc->worst_quality;
2499 int i;
2500
2501 // Look up the current projected bits per block for the base index
2502 const int base_bits_per_mb =
2503 vp9_rc_bits_per_mb(frame_type, qindex, 1.0, bit_depth);
2504
2505 // Find the target bits per mb based on the base value and given ratio.
2506 const int target_bits_per_mb = (int)(rate_target_ratio * base_bits_per_mb);
2507
2508 // Convert the q target to an index
2509 for (i = rc->best_quality; i < rc->worst_quality; ++i) {
2510 if (vp9_rc_bits_per_mb(frame_type, i, 1.0, bit_depth) <=
2511 target_bits_per_mb) {
2512 target_index = i;
2513 break;
2514 }
2515 }
2516 return target_index - qindex;
2517}

2519void vp9_rc_set_gf_interval_range(const VP9_COMP *const cpi,
2520 RATE_CONTROL *const rc) {
2521 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2522
2523 // Special case code for 1 pass fixed Q mode tests
2524 if ((oxcf->pass == 0) && (oxcf->rc_mode == VPX_Q)) {
2525 rc->max_gf_interval = FIXED_GF_INTERVAL;
2526 rc->min_gf_interval = FIXED_GF_INTERVAL;
2527 rc->static_scene_max_gf_interval = FIXED_GF_INTERVAL;
2528 } else {
2529 // Set Maximum gf/arf interval
2530 rc->max_gf_interval = oxcf->max_gf_interval;
2531 rc->min_gf_interval = oxcf->min_gf_interval;
2532#if CONFIG_RATE_CTRL
2533 if (rc->min_gf_interval == 0) {
2534 rc->min_gf_interval = vp9_rc_get_default_min_gf_interval(
2535 oxcf->width, oxcf->height, oxcf->init_framerate);
2536 }
2537 if (rc->max_gf_interval == 0) {
2538 rc->max_gf_interval = vp9_rc_get_default_max_gf_interval(
2539 oxcf->init_framerate, rc->min_gf_interval);
2540 }
2541#else
2542 if (rc->min_gf_interval == 0)
2543 rc->min_gf_interval = vp9_rc_get_default_min_gf_interval(
2544 oxcf->width, oxcf->height, cpi->framerate);
2545 if (rc->max_gf_interval == 0)
2546 rc->max_gf_interval = vp9_rc_get_default_max_gf_interval(
2547 cpi->framerate, rc->min_gf_interval);
2548#endif
2549
2550 // Extended max interval for genuinely static scenes like slide shows.
2551 rc->static_scene_max_gf_interval = MAX_STATIC_GF_GROUP_LENGTH;
2552
2553 if (rc->max_gf_interval > rc->static_scene_max_gf_interval)
2554 rc->max_gf_interval = rc->static_scene_max_gf_interval;
2555
2556 // Clamp min to max
2557 rc->min_gf_interval = VPXMIN(rc->min_gf_interval, rc->max_gf_interval);
2558
2559 if (oxcf->target_level == LEVEL_AUTO) {
2560 const uint32_t pic_size = cpi->common.width * cpi->common.height;
2561 const uint32_t pic_breadth =
2562 VPXMAX(cpi->common.width, cpi->common.height);
2563 int i;
2564 for (i = LEVEL_1; i < LEVEL_MAX; ++i) {
2565 if (vp9_level_defs[i].max_luma_picture_size >= pic_size &&
2566 vp9_level_defs[i].max_luma_picture_breadth >= pic_breadth) {
2567 if (rc->min_gf_interval <=
2568 (int)vp9_level_defs[i].min_altref_distance) {
2569 rc->min_gf_interval =
2570 (int)vp9_level_defs[i].min_altref_distance + 1;
2571 rc->max_gf_interval =
2572 VPXMAX(rc->max_gf_interval, rc->min_gf_interval);
2573 }
2574 break;
2575 }
2576 }
2577 }
2578 }

2581void vp9_rc_update_framerate(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2582 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2583 const VP9EncoderConfig *const oxcf = &cpi->oxcf;
2584 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2585 int vbr_max_bits;
2586
2587 rc->avg_frame_bandwidth = (int)(oxcf->target_bandwidth / cpi->framerate);
2588 rc->min_frame_bandwidth =
2589 (int)(rc->avg_frame_bandwidth * oxcf->two_pass_vbrmin_section / 100);
2590
2591 rc->min_frame_bandwidth =
2592 VPXMAX(rc->min_frame_bandwidth, FRAME_OVERHEAD_BITS);
2593
2594 // A maximum bitrate for a frame is defined.
2595 // However this limit is extended if a very high rate is given on the command
2596 // line or the rate can not be achieved because of a user specified max q
2597 // (e.g. when the user specifies lossless encode).
2598 //
2599 // If a level is specified that requires a lower maximum rate then the level
2600 // value take precedence.
2601 vbr_max_bits =
2602 (int)(((int64_t)rc->avg_frame_bandwidth * oxcf->two_pass_vbrmax_section) /
2603 100);
2604 rc->max_frame_bandwidth =
2605 VPXMAX(VPXMAX((cm->MBs * MAX_MB_RATE), MAXRATE_1080P), vbr_max_bits);
2606
2607 vp9_rc_set_gf_interval_range(cpi, rc);
2608}

2610#define VBR_PCT_ADJUSTMENT_LIMIT 50
2611// For VBR...adjustment to the frame target based on error from previous frames
2612static void vbr_rate_correction(VP9_COMP *cpi, int *this_frame_target) {
2613 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2614 int64_t vbr_bits_off_target = rc->vbr_bits_off_target;
2615 int max_delta;
2616 int frame_window = VPXMIN(16, ((int)cpi->twopass.total_stats.count -
2617 cpi->common.current_video_frame));
2618
2619 // Calcluate the adjustment to rate for this frame.
2620 if (frame_window > 0) {
2621 max_delta = (vbr_bits_off_target > 0)
2622 ? (int)(vbr_bits_off_target / frame_window)
2623 : (int)(-vbr_bits_off_target / frame_window);
2624
2625 max_delta = VPXMIN(max_delta,
2626 ((*this_frame_target * VBR_PCT_ADJUSTMENT_LIMIT) / 100));
2627
2628 // vbr_bits_off_target > 0 means we have extra bits to spend
2629 if (vbr_bits_off_target > 0) {
2630 *this_frame_target += (vbr_bits_off_target > max_delta)
2631 ? max_delta
2632 : (int)vbr_bits_off_target;
2633 } else {
2634 *this_frame_target -= (vbr_bits_off_target < -max_delta)
2635 ? max_delta
2636 : (int)-vbr_bits_off_target;
2637 }
2638 }
2639
2640 // Fast redistribution of bits arising from massive local undershoot.
2641 // Dont do it for kf,arf,gf or overlay frames.
2642 if (!frame_is_kf_gf_arf(cpi) && !rc->is_src_frame_alt_ref &&
2643 rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast) {
2644 int one_frame_bits = VPXMAX(rc->avg_frame_bandwidth, *this_frame_target);
2645 int fast_extra_bits;
2646 fast_extra_bits = (int)VPXMIN(rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast, one_frame_bits);
2647 fast_extra_bits = (int)VPXMIN(
2648 fast_extra_bits,
2649 VPXMAX(one_frame_bits / 8, rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast / 8));
2650 *this_frame_target += (int)fast_extra_bits;
2651 rc->vbr_bits_off_target_fast -= fast_extra_bits;
2652 }
2653}
2654
2655void vp9_set_target_rate(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2656 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2657 int target_rate = rc->base_frame_target;
2658
2659 if (cpi->common.frame_type == KEY_FRAME)
2660 target_rate = vp9_rc_clamp_iframe_target_size(cpi, target_rate);
2661 else
2662 target_rate = vp9_rc_clamp_pframe_target_size(cpi, target_rate);
2663
2664 if (!cpi->oxcf.vbr_corpus_complexity) {
2665 // Correction to rate target based on prior over or under shoot.
2666 if (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_VBR || cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_CQ)
2667 vbr_rate_correction(cpi, &target_rate);
2668 }
2669 vp9_rc_set_frame_target(cpi, target_rate);
2670}

2672// Check if we should resize, based on average QP from past x frames.
2673// Only allow for resize at most one scale down for now, scaling factor is 2.
2674int vp9_resize_one_pass_cbr(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2675 const VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2676 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2677 RESIZE_ACTION resize_action = NO_RESIZE;
2678 int avg_qp_thr1 = 70;
2679 int avg_qp_thr2 = 50;
2680 // Don't allow for resized frame to go below 320x180, resize in steps of 3/4.
2681 int min_width = (320 * 4) / 3;
2682 int min_height = (180 * 4) / 3;
2683 int down_size_on = 1;
2684 int force_downsize_rate = 0;
2685 cpi->resize_scale_num = 1;
2686 cpi->resize_scale_den = 1;
2687 // Don't resize on key frame; reset the counters on key frame.
2688 if (cm->frame_type == KEY_FRAME) {
2689 cpi->resize_avg_qp = 0;
2690 cpi->resize_count = 0;
2691 return 0;
2692 }
2693
2694 // No resizing down if frame size is below some limit.
2695 if ((cm->width * cm->height) < min_width * min_height) down_size_on = 0;
2696
2697#if CONFIG_VP9_TEMPORAL_DENOISING
2698 // If denoiser is on, apply a smaller qp threshold.
2699 if (cpi->oxcf.noise_sensitivity > 0) {
2700 avg_qp_thr1 = 60;
2701 avg_qp_thr2 = 40;
2702 }
2703#endif
2704
2705 // Force downsize based on per-frame-bandwidth, for extreme case,
2706 // for HD input.
2707 if (cpi->resize_state == ORIG && cm->width * cm->height >= 1280 * 720) {
2708 if (rc->avg_frame_bandwidth < 300000 / 30) {
2709 resize_action = DOWN_ONEHALF;
2710 cpi->resize_state = ONE_HALF;
2711 force_downsize_rate = 1;
2712 } else if (rc->avg_frame_bandwidth < 400000 / 30) {
2713 resize_action = ONEHALFONLY_RESIZE ? DOWN_ONEHALF : DOWN_THREEFOUR;
2714 cpi->resize_state = ONEHALFONLY_RESIZE ? ONE_HALF : THREE_QUARTER;
2715 force_downsize_rate = 1;
2716 }
2717 } else if (cpi->resize_state == THREE_QUARTER &&
2718 cm->width * cm->height >= 960 * 540) {
2719 if (rc->avg_frame_bandwidth < 300000 / 30) {
2720 resize_action = DOWN_ONEHALF;
2721 cpi->resize_state = ONE_HALF;
2722 force_downsize_rate = 1;
2723 }
2724 }
2725
2726 // Resize based on average buffer underflow and QP over some window.
2727 // Ignore samples close to key frame, since QP is usually high after key.
2728 if (!force_downsize_rate && cpi->rc.frames_since_key > cpi->framerate) {
2729 const int window = VPXMIN(30, (int)(2 * cpi->framerate));
2730 cpi->resize_avg_qp += rc->last_q[INTER_FRAME];
2731 if (cpi->rc.buffer_level < (int)(30 * rc->optimal_buffer_level / 100))
2732 ++cpi->resize_buffer_underflow;
2733 ++cpi->resize_count;
2734 // Check for resize action every "window" frames.
2735 if (cpi->resize_count >= window) {
2736 int avg_qp = cpi->resize_avg_qp / cpi->resize_count;
2737 // Resize down if buffer level has underflowed sufficient amount in past
2738 // window, and we are at original or 3/4 of original resolution.
2739 // Resize back up if average QP is low, and we are currently in a resized
2740 // down state, i.e. 1/2 or 3/4 of original resolution.
2741 // Currently, use a flag to turn 3/4 resizing feature on/off.
2742 if (cpi->resize_buffer_underflow > (cpi->resize_count >> 2) &&
2743 down_size_on) {
2744 if (cpi->resize_state == THREE_QUARTER) {
2745 resize_action = DOWN_ONEHALF;
2746 cpi->resize_state = ONE_HALF;
2747 } else if (cpi->resize_state == ORIG) {
2748 resize_action = ONEHALFONLY_RESIZE ? DOWN_ONEHALF : DOWN_THREEFOUR;
2749 cpi->resize_state = ONEHALFONLY_RESIZE ? ONE_HALF : THREE_QUARTER;
2750 }
2751 } else if (cpi->resize_state != ORIG &&
2752 avg_qp < avg_qp_thr1 * cpi->rc.worst_quality / 100) {
2753 if (cpi->resize_state == THREE_QUARTER ||
2754 avg_qp < avg_qp_thr2 * cpi->rc.worst_quality / 100 ||
2755 ONEHALFONLY_RESIZE) {
2756 resize_action = UP_ORIG;
2757 cpi->resize_state = ORIG;
2758 } else if (cpi->resize_state == ONE_HALF) {
2759 resize_action = UP_THREEFOUR;
2760 cpi->resize_state = THREE_QUARTER;
2761 }
2762 }
2763 // Reset for next window measurement.
2764 cpi->resize_avg_qp = 0;
2765 cpi->resize_count = 0;
2766 cpi->resize_buffer_underflow = 0;
2767 }
2768 }
2769 // If decision is to resize, reset some quantities, and check is we should
2770 // reduce rate correction factor,
2771 if (resize_action != NO_RESIZE) {
2772 int target_bits_per_frame;
2773 int active_worst_quality;
2774 int qindex;
2775 int tot_scale_change;
2776 if (resize_action == DOWN_THREEFOUR || resize_action == UP_THREEFOUR) {
2777 cpi->resize_scale_num = 3;
2778 cpi->resize_scale_den = 4;
2779 } else if (resize_action == DOWN_ONEHALF) {
2780 cpi->resize_scale_num = 1;
2781 cpi->resize_scale_den = 2;
2782 } else { // UP_ORIG or anything else
2783 cpi->resize_scale_num = 1;
2784 cpi->resize_scale_den = 1;
2785 }
2786 tot_scale_change = (cpi->resize_scale_den * cpi->resize_scale_den) /
2787 (cpi->resize_scale_num * cpi->resize_scale_num);
2788 // Reset buffer level to optimal, update target size.
2789 rc->buffer_level = rc->optimal_buffer_level;
2790 rc->bits_off_target = rc->optimal_buffer_level;
2791 rc->this_frame_target = vp9_calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2792 // Get the projected qindex, based on the scaled target frame size (scaled
2793 // so target_bits_per_mb in vp9_rc_regulate_q will be correct target).
2794 target_bits_per_frame = (resize_action >= 0)
2795 ? rc->this_frame_target * tot_scale_change
2796 : rc->this_frame_target / tot_scale_change;
2797 active_worst_quality = calc_active_worst_quality_one_pass_cbr(cpi);
2798 qindex = vp9_rc_regulate_q(cpi, target_bits_per_frame, rc->best_quality,
2799 active_worst_quality);
2800 // If resize is down, check if projected q index is close to worst_quality,
2801 // and if so, reduce the rate correction factor (since likely can afford
2802 // lower q for resized frame).
2803 if (resize_action > 0 && qindex > 90 * cpi->rc.worst_quality / 100) {
2804 rc->rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL] *= 0.85;
2805 }
2806 // If resize is back up, check if projected q index is too much above the
2807 // current base_qindex, and if so, reduce the rate correction factor
2808 // (since prefer to keep q for resized frame at least close to previous q).
2809 if (resize_action < 0 && qindex > 130 * cm->base_qindex / 100) {
2810 rc->rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL] *= 0.9;
2811 }
2812 }
2813 return resize_action;
2814}
2815
2816static void adjust_gf_boost_lag_one_pass_vbr(VP9_COMP *cpi,
2817 uint64_t avg_sad_current) {
2818 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2819 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2820 int target;
2821 int found = 0;
2822 int found2 = 0;
2823 int frame;
2824 int i;
2825 uint64_t avg_source_sad_lag = avg_sad_current;
2826 int high_source_sad_lagindex = -1;
2827 int steady_sad_lagindex = -1;
2828 uint32_t sad_thresh1 = 70000;
2829 uint32_t sad_thresh2 = 120000;
2830 int low_content = 0;
2831 int high_content = 0;
2832 double rate_err = 1.0;
2833 // Get measure of complexity over the future frames, and get the first
2834 // future frame with high_source_sad/scene-change.
2835 int tot_frames = (int)vp9_lookahead_depth(cpi->lookahead) - 1;
2836 for (frame = tot_frames; frame >= 1; --frame) {
2837 const int lagframe_idx = tot_frames - frame + 1;
2838 uint64_t reference_sad = rc->avg_source_sad[0];
2839 for (i = 1; i < lagframe_idx; ++i) {
2840 if (rc->avg_source_sad[i] > 0)
2841 reference_sad = (3 * reference_sad + rc->avg_source_sad[i]) >> 2;
2842 }
2843 // Detect up-coming scene change.
2844 if (!found &&
2845 (rc->avg_source_sad[lagframe_idx] >
2846 VPXMAX(sad_thresh1, (unsigned int)(reference_sad << 1)) ||
2847 rc->avg_source_sad[lagframe_idx] >
2848 VPXMAX(3 * sad_thresh1 >> 2,
2849 (unsigned int)(reference_sad << 2)))) {
2850 high_source_sad_lagindex = lagframe_idx;
2851 found = 1;
2852 }
2853 // Detect change from motion to steady.
2854 if (!found2 && lagframe_idx > 1 && lagframe_idx < tot_frames &&
2855 rc->avg_source_sad[lagframe_idx - 1] > (sad_thresh1 >> 2)) {
2856 found2 = 1;
2857 for (i = lagframe_idx; i < tot_frames; ++i) {
2858 if (!(rc->avg_source_sad[i] > 0 &&
2859 rc->avg_source_sad[i] < (sad_thresh1 >> 2) &&
2860 rc->avg_source_sad[i] <
2861 (rc->avg_source_sad[lagframe_idx - 1] >> 1))) {
2862 found2 = 0;
2863 i = tot_frames;
2864 }
2865 }
2866 if (found2) steady_sad_lagindex = lagframe_idx;
2867 }
2868 avg_source_sad_lag += rc->avg_source_sad[lagframe_idx];
2869 }
2870 if (tot_frames > 0) avg_source_sad_lag = avg_source_sad_lag / tot_frames;
2871 // Constrain distance between detected scene cuts.
2872 if (high_source_sad_lagindex != -1 &&
2873 high_source_sad_lagindex != rc->high_source_sad_lagindex - 1 &&
2874 abs(high_source_sad_lagindex - rc->high_source_sad_lagindex) < 4)
2875 rc->high_source_sad_lagindex = -1;
2876 else
2877 rc->high_source_sad_lagindex = high_source_sad_lagindex;
2878 // Adjust some factors for the next GF group, ignore initial key frame,
2879 // and only for lag_in_frames not too small.
2880 if (cpi->refresh_golden_frame == 1 && cm->current_video_frame > 30 &&
2881 cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames > 8) {
2882 int frame_constraint;
2883 if (rc->rolling_target_bits > 0)
2884 rate_err =
2885 (double)rc->rolling_actual_bits / (double)rc->rolling_target_bits;
2886 high_content = high_source_sad_lagindex != -1 ||
2887 avg_source_sad_lag > (rc->prev_avg_source_sad_lag << 1) ||
2888 avg_source_sad_lag > sad_thresh2;
2889 low_content = high_source_sad_lagindex == -1 &&
2890 ((avg_source_sad_lag < (rc->prev_avg_source_sad_lag >> 1)) ||
2891 (avg_source_sad_lag < sad_thresh1));
2892 if (low_content) {
2893 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST;
2894 rc->baseline_gf_interval =
2895 VPXMIN(15, (3 * rc->baseline_gf_interval) >> 1);
2896 } else if (high_content) {
2897 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST >> 1;
2898 rc->baseline_gf_interval = (rate_err > 3.0)
2899 ? VPXMAX(10, rc->baseline_gf_interval >> 1)
2900 : VPXMAX(6, rc->baseline_gf_interval >> 1);
2901 }
2902 if (rc->baseline_gf_interval > cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames - 1)
2903 rc->baseline_gf_interval = cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames - 1;
2904 // Check for constraining gf_interval for up-coming scene/content changes,
2905 // or for up-coming key frame, whichever is closer.
2906 frame_constraint = rc->frames_to_key;
2907 if (rc->high_source_sad_lagindex > 0 &&
2908 frame_constraint > rc->high_source_sad_lagindex)
2909 frame_constraint = rc->high_source_sad_lagindex;
2910 if (steady_sad_lagindex > 3 && frame_constraint > steady_sad_lagindex)
2911 frame_constraint = steady_sad_lagindex;
2912 adjust_gfint_frame_constraint(cpi, frame_constraint);
2913 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2914 // Adjust factors for active_worst setting & af_ratio for next gf interval.
2915 rc->fac_active_worst_inter = 150; // corresponds to 3/2 (= 150 /100).
2916 rc->fac_active_worst_gf = 100;
2917 if (rate_err < 2.0 && !high_content) {
2918 rc->fac_active_worst_inter = 120;
2919 rc->fac_active_worst_gf = 90;
2920 } else if (rate_err > 8.0 && rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] < 16) {
2921 // Increase active_worst faster at low Q if rate fluctuation is high.
2922 rc->fac_active_worst_inter = 200;
2923 if (rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] < 8)
2924 rc->fac_active_worst_inter = 400;
2925 }
2926 if (low_content && rc->avg_frame_low_motion > 80) {
2927 rc->af_ratio_onepass_vbr = 15;
2928 } else if (high_content || rc->avg_frame_low_motion < 30) {
2929 rc->af_ratio_onepass_vbr = 5;
2930 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST >> 2;
2931 }
2932 if (cpi->sf.use_altref_onepass && cpi->oxcf.enable_auto_arf) {
2933 // Flag to disable usage of ARF based on past usage, only allow this
2934 // disabling if current frame/group does not start with key frame or
2935 // scene cut. Note perc_arf_usage is only computed for speed >= 5.
2936 int arf_usage_low =
2937 (cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME && !rc->high_source_sad &&
2938 cpi->rc.perc_arf_usage < 15 && cpi->oxcf.speed >= 5);
2939 // Don't use alt-ref for this group under certain conditions.
2940 if (arf_usage_low ||
2941 (rc->high_source_sad_lagindex > 0 &&
2942 rc->high_source_sad_lagindex <= rc->frames_till_gf_update_due) ||
2943 (avg_source_sad_lag > 3 * sad_thresh1 >> 3)) {
2944 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 0;
2945 rc->alt_ref_gf_group = 0;
2946 } else {
2947 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 1;
2948 rc->alt_ref_gf_group = 1;
2949 // If alt-ref is used for this gf group, limit the interval.
2950 if (rc->baseline_gf_interval > 12) {
2951 rc->baseline_gf_interval = 12;
2952 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
2953 }
2954 }
2955 }
2956 target = calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_vbr(cpi);
2957 vp9_rc_set_frame_target(cpi, target);
2958 }
2959 rc->prev_avg_source_sad_lag = avg_source_sad_lag;
2960}
2961
2962// Compute average source sad (temporal sad: between current source and
2963// previous source) over a subset of superblocks. Use this is detect big changes
2964// in content and allow rate control to react.
2965// This function also handles special case of lag_in_frames, to measure content
2966// level in #future frames set by the lag_in_frames.
2967void vp9_scene_detection_onepass(VP9_COMP *cpi) {
2968 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
2969 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
2970 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG const *unscaled_src = cpi->un_scaled_source;
2971 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG const *unscaled_last_src = cpi->unscaled_last_source;
2972 uint8_t *src_y;
2973 int src_ystride;
2974 int src_width;
2975 int src_height;
2976 uint8_t *last_src_y;
2977 int last_src_ystride;
2978 int last_src_width;
2979 int last_src_height;
2980 if (cpi->un_scaled_source == NULL || cpi->unscaled_last_source == NULL ||
2981 (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.current_superframe == 0))
2982 return;
2983 src_y = unscaled_src->y_buffer;
2984 src_ystride = unscaled_src->y_stride;
2985 src_width = unscaled_src->y_width;
2986 src_height = unscaled_src->y_height;
2987 last_src_y = unscaled_last_src->y_buffer;
2988 last_src_ystride = unscaled_last_src->y_stride;
2989 last_src_width = unscaled_last_src->y_width;
2990 last_src_height = unscaled_last_src->y_height;
2991#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
2992 if (cm->use_highbitdepth) return;
2993#endif
2994 rc->high_source_sad = 0;
2995 rc->high_num_blocks_with_motion = 0;
2996 // For SVC: scene detection is only checked on first spatial layer of
2997 // the superframe using the original/unscaled resolutions.
2998 if (cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == cpi->svc.first_spatial_layer_to_encode &&
2999 src_width == last_src_width && src_height == last_src_height) {
3000 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG *frames[MAX_LAG_BUFFERS] = { NULL };
3001 int num_mi_cols = cm->mi_cols;
3002 int num_mi_rows = cm->mi_rows;
3003 int start_frame = 0;
3004 int frames_to_buffer = 1;
3005 int frame = 0;
3006 int scene_cut_force_key_frame = 0;
3007 int num_zero_temp_sad = 0;
3008 uint64_t avg_sad_current = 0;
3009 uint32_t min_thresh = 20000; // ~5 * 64 * 64
3010 float thresh = 8.0f;
3011 uint32_t thresh_key = 140000;
3012 if (cpi->oxcf.speed <= 5) thresh_key = 240000;
3013 if (cpi->oxcf.content != VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN) min_thresh = 65000;
3014 if (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_VBR) thresh = 2.1f;
3015 if (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers > 1) {
3016 const int aligned_width = ALIGN_POWER_OF_TWO(src_width, MI_SIZE_LOG2);
3017 const int aligned_height = ALIGN_POWER_OF_TWO(src_height, MI_SIZE_LOG2);
3018 num_mi_cols = aligned_width >> MI_SIZE_LOG2;
3019 num_mi_rows = aligned_height >> MI_SIZE_LOG2;
3020 }
3021 if (cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames > 0) {
3022 frames_to_buffer = (cm->current_video_frame == 1)
3023 ? (int)vp9_lookahead_depth(cpi->lookahead) - 1
3024 : 2;
3025 start_frame = (int)vp9_lookahead_depth(cpi->lookahead) - 1;
3026 for (frame = 0; frame < frames_to_buffer; ++frame) {
3027 const int lagframe_idx = start_frame - frame;
3028 if (lagframe_idx >= 0) {
3029 struct lookahead_entry *buf =
3030 vp9_lookahead_peek(cpi->lookahead, lagframe_idx);
3031 frames[frame] = &buf->img;
3032 }
3033 }
3034 // The avg_sad for this current frame is the value of frame#1
3035 // (first future frame) from previous frame.
3036 avg_sad_current = rc->avg_source_sad[1];
3037 if (avg_sad_current >
3038 VPXMAX(min_thresh,
3039 (unsigned int)(rc->avg_source_sad[0] * thresh)) &&
3040 cm->current_video_frame > (unsigned int)cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames)
3041 rc->high_source_sad = 1;
3042 else
3043 rc->high_source_sad = 0;
3044 if (rc->high_source_sad && avg_sad_current > thresh_key)
3045 scene_cut_force_key_frame = 1;
3046 // Update recursive average for current frame.
3047 if (avg_sad_current > 0)
3048 rc->avg_source_sad[0] =
3049 (3 * rc->avg_source_sad[0] + avg_sad_current) >> 2;
3050 // Shift back data, starting at frame#1.
3051 for (frame = 1; frame < cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames - 1; ++frame)
3052 rc->avg_source_sad[frame] = rc->avg_source_sad[frame + 1];
3053 }
3054 for (frame = 0; frame < frames_to_buffer; ++frame) {
3055 if (cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames == 0 ||
3056 (frames[frame] != NULL && frames[frame + 1] != NULL &&
3057 frames[frame]->y_width == frames[frame + 1]->y_width &&
3058 frames[frame]->y_height == frames[frame + 1]->y_height)) {
3059 int sbi_row, sbi_col;
3060 const int lagframe_idx =
3061 (cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames == 0) ? 0 : start_frame - frame + 1;
3062 const BLOCK_SIZE bsize = BLOCK_64X64;
3063 // Loop over sub-sample of frame, compute average sad over 64x64 blocks.
3064 uint64_t avg_sad = 0;
3065 uint64_t tmp_sad = 0;
3066 int num_samples = 0;
3067 int sb_cols = (num_mi_cols + MI_BLOCK_SIZE - 1) / MI_BLOCK_SIZE;
3068 int sb_rows = (num_mi_rows + MI_BLOCK_SIZE - 1) / MI_BLOCK_SIZE;
3069 if (cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames > 0) {
3070 src_y = frames[frame]->y_buffer;
3071 src_ystride = frames[frame]->y_stride;
3072 last_src_y = frames[frame + 1]->y_buffer;
3073 last_src_ystride = frames[frame + 1]->y_stride;
3074 }
3075 num_zero_temp_sad = 0;
3076 for (sbi_row = 0; sbi_row < sb_rows; ++sbi_row) {
3077 for (sbi_col = 0; sbi_col < sb_cols; ++sbi_col) {
3078 // Checker-board pattern, ignore boundary.
3079 if (((sbi_row > 0 && sbi_col > 0) &&
3080 (sbi_row < sb_rows - 1 && sbi_col < sb_cols - 1) &&
3081 ((sbi_row % 2 == 0 && sbi_col % 2 == 0) ||
3082 (sbi_row % 2 != 0 && sbi_col % 2 != 0)))) {
3083 tmp_sad = cpi->fn_ptr[bsize].sdf(src_y, src_ystride, last_src_y,
3084 last_src_ystride);
3085 avg_sad += tmp_sad;
3086 num_samples++;
3087 if (tmp_sad == 0) num_zero_temp_sad++;
3088 }
3089 src_y += 64;
3090 last_src_y += 64;
3091 }
3092 src_y += (src_ystride << 6) - (sb_cols << 6);
3093 last_src_y += (last_src_ystride << 6) - (sb_cols << 6);
3094 }
3095 if (num_samples > 0) avg_sad = avg_sad / num_samples;
3096 // Set high_source_sad flag if we detect very high increase in avg_sad
3097 // between current and previous frame value(s). Use minimum threshold
3098 // for cases where there is small change from content that is completely
3099 // static.
3100 if (lagframe_idx == 0) {
3101 if (avg_sad >
3102 VPXMAX(min_thresh,
3103 (unsigned int)(rc->avg_source_sad[0] * thresh)) &&
3104 rc->frames_since_key > 1 + cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers &&
3105 num_zero_temp_sad < 3 * (num_samples >> 2))
3106 rc->high_source_sad = 1;
3107 else
3108 rc->high_source_sad = 0;
3109 if (rc->high_source_sad && avg_sad > thresh_key)
3110 scene_cut_force_key_frame = 1;
3111 if (avg_sad > 0 || cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_CBR)
3112 rc->avg_source_sad[0] = (3 * rc->avg_source_sad[0] + avg_sad) >> 2;
3113 } else {
3114 rc->avg_source_sad[lagframe_idx] = avg_sad;
3115 }
3116 if (num_zero_temp_sad < (3 * num_samples >> 2))
3117 rc->high_num_blocks_with_motion = 1;
3118 }
3119 }
3120 // For CBR non-screen content mode, check if we should reset the rate
3121 // control. Reset is done if high_source_sad is detected and the rate
3122 // control is at very low QP with rate correction factor at min level.
3123 if (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_CBR &&
3124 cpi->oxcf.content != VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN && !cpi->use_svc) {
3125 if (rc->high_source_sad && rc->last_q[INTER_FRAME] == rc->best_quality &&
3126 rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] < (rc->best_quality << 1) &&
3127 rc->rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL] == MIN_BPB_FACTOR) {
3128 rc->rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL] = 0.5;
3129 rc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] = rc->worst_quality;
3130 rc->buffer_level = rc->optimal_buffer_level;
3131 rc->bits_off_target = rc->optimal_buffer_level;
3132 rc->reset_high_source_sad = 1;
3133 }
3134 if (cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME && rc->reset_high_source_sad)
3135 rc->this_frame_target = rc->avg_frame_bandwidth;
3136 }
3137 // For SVC the new (updated) avg_source_sad[0] for the current superframe
3138 // updates the setting for all layers.
3139 if (cpi->use_svc) {
3140 int sl, tl;
3141 SVC *const svc = &cpi->svc;
3142 for (sl = 0; sl < svc->number_spatial_layers; ++sl)
3143 for (tl = 0; tl < svc->number_temporal_layers; ++tl) {
3144 int layer = LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(sl, tl, svc->number_temporal_layers);
3145 LAYER_CONTEXT *const lc = &svc->layer_context[layer];
3146 RATE_CONTROL *const lrc = &lc->rc;
3147 lrc->avg_source_sad[0] = rc->avg_source_sad[0];
3148 }
3149 }
3150 // For VBR, under scene change/high content change, force golden refresh.
3151 if (cpi->oxcf.rc_mode == VPX_VBR && cm->frame_type != KEY_FRAME &&
3152 rc->high_source_sad && rc->frames_to_key > 3 &&
3153 rc->count_last_scene_change > 4 &&
3154 cpi->ext_refresh_frame_flags_pending == 0) {
3155 int target;
3156 cpi->refresh_golden_frame = 1;
3157 if (scene_cut_force_key_frame) cm->frame_type = KEY_FRAME;
3158 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 0;
3159 if (cpi->sf.use_altref_onepass && cpi->oxcf.enable_auto_arf)
3160 rc->source_alt_ref_pending = 1;
3161 rc->gfu_boost = DEFAULT_GF_BOOST >> 1;
3162 rc->baseline_gf_interval =
3163 VPXMIN(20, VPXMAX(10, rc->baseline_gf_interval));
3164 adjust_gfint_frame_constraint(cpi, rc->frames_to_key);
3165 rc->frames_till_gf_update_due = rc->baseline_gf_interval;
3166 target = calc_pframe_target_size_one_pass_vbr(cpi);
3167 vp9_rc_set_frame_target(cpi, target);
3168 rc->count_last_scene_change = 0;
3169 } else {
3170 rc->count_last_scene_change++;
3171 }
3172 // If lag_in_frame is used, set the gf boost and interval.
3173 if (cpi->oxcf.lag_in_frames > 0)
3174 adjust_gf_boost_lag_one_pass_vbr(cpi, avg_sad_current);
3175 }
3176}
3177
3178// Test if encoded frame will significantly overshoot the target bitrate, and
3179// if so, set the QP, reset/adjust some rate control parameters, and return 1.
3180// frame_size = -1 means frame has not been encoded.
3181int vp9_encodedframe_overshoot(VP9_COMP *cpi, int frame_size, int *q) {
3182 VP9_COMMON *const cm = &cpi->common;
3183 RATE_CONTROL *const rc = &cpi->rc;
3184 SPEED_FEATURES *const sf = &cpi->sf;
3185 int thresh_qp = 7 * (rc->worst_quality >> 3);
3186 int thresh_rate = rc->avg_frame_bandwidth << 3;
3187 // Lower thresh_qp for video (more overshoot at lower Q) to be
3188 // more conservative for video.
3189 if (cpi->oxcf.content != VP9E_CONTENT_SCREEN)
3190 thresh_qp = 3 * (rc->worst_quality >> 2);
3191 // If this decision is not based on an encoded frame size but just on
3192 // scene/slide change detection (i.e., re_encode_overshoot_cbr_rt ==
3193 // FAST_DETECTION_MAXQ), for now skip the (frame_size > thresh_rate)
3194 // condition in this case.
3195 // TODO(marpan): Use a better size/rate condition for this case and
3196 // adjust thresholds.
3197 if ((sf->overshoot_detection_cbr_rt == FAST_DETECTION_MAXQ ||
3198 frame_size > thresh_rate) &&
3199 cm->base_qindex < thresh_qp) {
3200 double rate_correction_factor =
3201 cpi->rc.rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL];
3202 const int target_size = cpi->rc.avg_frame_bandwidth;
3203 double new_correction_factor;
3204 int target_bits_per_mb;
3205 double q2;
3206 int enumerator;
3207 // Force a re-encode, and for now use max-QP.
3208 *q = cpi->rc.worst_quality;
3209 cpi->cyclic_refresh->counter_encode_maxq_scene_change = 0;
3210 cpi->rc.re_encode_maxq_scene_change = 1;
3211 // If the frame_size is much larger than the threshold (big content change)
3212 // and the encoded frame used alot of Intra modes, then force hybrid_intra
3213 // encoding for the re-encode on this scene change. hybrid_intra will
3214 // use rd-based intra mode selection for small blocks.
3215 if (sf->overshoot_detection_cbr_rt == RE_ENCODE_MAXQ &&
3216 frame_size > (thresh_rate << 1) && cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id == 0) {
3217 MODE_INFO **mi = cm->mi_grid_visible;
3218 int sum_intra_usage = 0;
3219 int mi_row, mi_col;
3220 int tot = 0;
3221 for (mi_row = 0; mi_row < cm->mi_rows; mi_row++) {
3222 for (mi_col = 0; mi_col < cm->mi_cols; mi_col++) {
3223 if (mi[0]->ref_frame[0] == INTRA_FRAME) sum_intra_usage++;
3224 tot++;
3225 mi++;
3226 }
3227 mi += 8;
3228 }
3229 sum_intra_usage = 100 * sum_intra_usage / (cm->mi_rows * cm->mi_cols);
3230 if (sum_intra_usage > 60) cpi->rc.hybrid_intra_scene_change = 1;
3231 }
3232 // Adjust avg_frame_qindex, buffer_level, and rate correction factors, as
3233 // these parameters will affect QP selection for subsequent frames. If they
3234 // have settled down to a very different (low QP) state, then not adjusting
3235 // them may cause next frame to select low QP and overshoot again.
3236 cpi->rc.avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] = *q;
3237 rc->buffer_level = rc->optimal_buffer_level;
3238 rc->bits_off_target = rc->optimal_buffer_level;
3239 // Reset rate under/over-shoot flags.
3240 cpi->rc.rc_1_frame = 0;
3241 cpi->rc.rc_2_frame = 0;
3242 // Adjust rate correction factor.
3243 target_bits_per_mb =
3244 (int)(((uint64_t)target_size << BPER_MB_NORMBITS) / cm->MBs);
3245 // Rate correction factor based on target_bits_per_mb and qp (==max_QP).
3246 // This comes from the inverse computation of vp9_rc_bits_per_mb().
3247 q2 = vp9_convert_qindex_to_q(*q, cm->bit_depth);
3248 enumerator = 1800000; // Factor for inter frame.
3249 enumerator += (int)(enumerator * q2) >> 12;
3250 new_correction_factor = (double)target_bits_per_mb * q2 / enumerator;
3251 if (new_correction_factor > rate_correction_factor) {
3252 rate_correction_factor =
3253 VPXMIN(2.0 * rate_correction_factor, new_correction_factor);
3254 if (rate_correction_factor > MAX_BPB_FACTOR)
3255 rate_correction_factor = MAX_BPB_FACTOR;
3256 cpi->rc.rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL] = rate_correction_factor;
3257 }
3258 // For temporal layers, reset the rate control parametes across all
3259 // temporal layers. If the first_spatial_layer_to_encode > 0, then this
3260 // superframe has skipped lower base layers. So in this case we should also
3261 // reset and force max-q for spatial layers < first_spatial_layer_to_encode.
3262 if (cpi->use_svc) {
3263 int tl = 0;
3264 int sl = 0;
3265 SVC *svc = &cpi->svc;
3266 for (sl = 0; sl < VPXMAX(1, svc->first_spatial_layer_to_encode); ++sl) {
3267 for (tl = 0; tl < svc->number_temporal_layers; ++tl) {
3268 const int layer =
3269 LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(sl, tl, svc->number_temporal_layers);
3270 LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = &svc->layer_context[layer];
3271 RATE_CONTROL *lrc = &lc->rc;
3272 lrc->avg_frame_qindex[INTER_FRAME] = *q;
3273 lrc->buffer_level = lrc->optimal_buffer_level;
3274 lrc->bits_off_target = lrc->optimal_buffer_level;
3275 lrc->rc_1_frame = 0;
3276 lrc->rc_2_frame = 0;
3277 lrc->rate_correction_factors[INTER_NORMAL] = rate_correction_factor;
3278 lrc->force_max_q = 1;
3279 }
3280 }
3281 }
3282 return 1;
3283 } else {
3284 return 0;
3285 }
